        <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-red-brand mb-2">Compliance · April 2026 · 12 min read</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4 leading-tight">Fire Extinguisher Inspection in Houston, TX: What Every Business Owner Needs to Know</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Houston is the energy capital of the world — and one of the most complex fire protection compliance environments in the United States. Whether you manage a restaurant in Midtown, a warehouse near the Ship Channel, or an office tower in the Galleria district, your fire extinguishers are a legal requirement with inspection schedules enforced by the Houston Fire Department. Here's exactly what NFPA 10 and Houston's local fire code require, what inspections cost, and what happens if you fall out of compliance.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">Houston Fire Extinguisher Inspection Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of Houston adopts the International Fire Code (IFC) with local amendments, enforced through the Houston Fire Department. Under this framework, all commercial properties must maintain portable fire extinguishers in compliance with <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10: Standard for Portable Fire Extinguishers</a>. Four inspection intervals apply to every commercial extinguisher in Houston.</p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Monthly Visual Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Monthly visual inspections can be performed by your own trained building staff — no license required. The check is simple: verify each extinguisher is in its designated location, unobstructed, the pressure gauge reads in the operating range, the tamper seal is intact, and the pull pin is in place. Document every monthly check. In the event of a fire incident or an enforcement action, the absence of monthly inspection records significantly increases your liability exposure.</p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Annual Professional Inspections</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Annual inspections must be performed by a technician holding a current Portable Fire Extinguisher license from the Texas Department of Insurance (TDI) State Fire Marshal's Office. The technician inspects the mechanical parts, extinguishing agent condition, pressure gauge, hose and nozzle integrity, and overall unit condition. They attach a dated service tag and document the inspection. Any unit that fails must be immediately serviced, recharged, or replaced — it cannot remain in service with a failed annual inspection.</p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">6-Year Internal Examination</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every six years, stored-pressure extinguishers must be emptied, disassembled, and internally examined. Houston's gulf coast humidity accelerates internal corrosion in extinguisher cylinders — particularly in coastal and port-adjacent facilities where salt air penetrates. The 6-year examination catches corrosion and agent degradation that external inspections miss. It typically includes a complete recharge after the internal inspection.</p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">12-Year Hydrostatic Testing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">At 12 years, extinguisher cylinders must undergo hydrostatic pressure testing to verify structural integrity under pressurization well above normal operating pressure. Units that fail must be condemned — they cannot be returned to service. After passing, units are recharged and marked with the new test date. In Houston's industrial corridor, where extinguishers may be exposed to heat, humidity, and chemical environments, the 12-year test is not a formality — units regularly fail.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Fire Extinguisher Inspection Costs in Houston, TX</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">Houston's large and competitive fire protection service market keeps inspection costs reasonable. Here's what to budget per unit:</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead><tr class="bg-gray-50"><th class="text-left p-3 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Service</th><th class="text-left p-3 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Cost Range (Per Unit)</th><th class="text-left p-3 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Frequency</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">Annual Inspection & Tag</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$15–$40</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Every 12 months</td></tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">Recharge (ABC Dry Chemical)</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$20–$50</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">As needed / after use</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">6-Year Internal Examination</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$25–$60</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Every 6 years</td></tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">12-Year Hydrostatic Test</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$35–$80</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Every 12 years</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">New Extinguisher (10 lb ABC)</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$45–$95</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Replacement</td></tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">Class K Kitchen Extinguisher</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200">$85–$180</td><td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Required in commercial kitchens</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Most Houston-area service providers offer volume pricing for properties with 20 or more extinguishers. If you manage multiple commercial properties across Houston, consolidating fire extinguisher service with a single provider can reduce per-unit costs by 20–35%.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Houston's Industrial and Petrochemical Facilities: Additional Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Standard ABC dry chemical extinguishers don't cover all hazard classes present in Houston's unique commercial environment. Properties along the Houston Ship Channel, in the Texas Medical Center, and in the industrial corridors of South and East Houston often require specialized extinguisher types:</p>
