            'Expired inspection tags — the most frequently cited violation. Any extinguisher with a service tag older than 12 months is out of compliance.',
            'Wrong extinguisher class for the hazard — ABC extinguishers in commercial kitchens without a dedicated Class K unit is a common violation in Houston restaurants.',
            'Obstructed access — extinguishers must be accessible with no obstruction within 3 feet and visible without searching.',
            'Missing or discharged tamper seals — indicates potential partial discharge or tampering.',
            'Excessive travel distance — 75 feet maximum for Class A, 50 feet for Class B, 30 feet for Class K in commercial kitchens.',
