          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Verify fire extinguisher contractor licensing at tdi.texas.gov/fire</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Penalties for Non-Compliance in Houston</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>First violation:</strong> Notice of Violation with correction period — typically 30 days. No fine if corrected promptly.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Uncorrected violations:</strong> Fines starting at $500 per violation per day. A property with 20 non-compliant extinguishers could face $10,000 per day in cumulative fines.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Serious deficiencies:</strong> The Houston Fire Marshal can issue occupancy restrictions or vacate orders for properties with egregious fire safety deficiencies. This is rare but enforced in Houston's densely occupied commercial zones.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8">
          {[
            { q: 'How often do fire extinguishers need to be inspected in Houston, TX?', a: 'Monthly visual checks (by staff), annual professional inspections by a TDI-licensed technician, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing per NFPA 10.' },
            { q: 'How much does a fire extinguisher inspection cost in Houston, TX?', a: 'Annual inspections run $15–$40 per unit in the Houston metro. 6-year internals cost $25–$60 per unit. 12-year hydrostatic tests cost $35–$80 per unit. Volume discounts apply for 20+ units.' },
